@push_leverage_positions
title: Push for more positions
view-if: parlament_coalition_leverage < 10
choose-if: parlament_coalition_push < ciu_erc_coalition_phase and ciu_erc_coalition_phase < 3
unavailable-subtitle: We've already pushed for more demands. [? if ciu_erc_coalition_phase < 3: We'll have to wait for the next round of negotiations to try again. ?]
on-arrival: {!
    if (Q.ciu_erc_coalition_phase == 1) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_leverage += 4;
        Q[Q.parlament_current_ciu + "_relations"] -= 5;
    } else {
        Q.parlament_coalition_leverage += 4;
        Q[Q.parlament_current_ciu + "_relations"] -= 3;
    }
    Q.parlament_coalition_push += 1;
!}
go-to: changes

@send_back
title: Send this counter-proposal
view-if: parlament_coalition_changes or parlament_coalition_concessions
subtitle: [?if parlament_coalition_push >= ciu_erc_coalition_phase: Back-and-forth negotiations will take some time, but may give us the extra edge needed for a better deal. ?]
on-arrival: {!
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = true;
    if (Q.parlament_coalition_push >= Q.ciu_erc_coalition_phase) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false;
    } else {
        if (Q.parlament_current_ciu_s > 40) {
            Q[Q.parlament_current_ciu + "_relations"] -= 2;
            if (Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_vp == "erc" || Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_interior == "erc" || Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_economy == "erc") {
                Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false;
            }
        } else {
            if (Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_vp != "erc" && Q.ciu_erc_coalition_phase != 3) {
                Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false;
            } 
            if ((Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_interior == "erc" || Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_economy == "erc") && Q.ciu_erc_coalition_phase != 3) {
                Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false;
            }
        }
    }
!}
go-to: decision

@decision
title: decision
go-to: accept if parlament_coalition_proposal_accept; next_phase if parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false

@next_phase
title: next phase
go-to: new_elections if ciu_erc_coalition_phase >= 3; new_phase_2 if not ciu_erc_coalition_phase >= 3

@new_phase_2
on-arrival: {!
    Q.ciu_erc_coalition_phase += 1;
    Q.month_actions += 1;
    Q.independence_trust -= 5;
!} 

[+ parlament_current_ciu +]'s representatives were initially dubious about our new proposal[? if parlament_current_ciu_s > 40 and parlament_coalition_proposal_vp = "erc" or parlament_coalition_proposal_economy = "erc" or parlament_coalition_proposal_interior = "erc": . Given the parliamentary arithmetics, they were reticent about ?][? if parlament_current_ciu_s <= 40 and parlament_coalition_proposal_vp != "erc" or parlament_coalition_proposal_economy = "erc" or parlament_coalition_proposal_interior = "erc": . They seemed reticent about ?][? if parlament_coalition_proposal_vp = "erc" and parlament_current_ciu_s > 40: giving up the Vice-Presidency?][? if parlament_coalition_proposal_vp != "erc" and parlament_current_ciu_s <= 40: us giving up the Vice-Presidency?][? if parlament_coalition_proposal_interior = "erc": [? if parlament_coalition_proposal_vp = "erc" : [? if parlament_coalition_proposal_economy != "erc": and ?][? if parlament_coalition_proposal_economy = "erc": , ?]?]giving up Interior ?][? if parlament_coalition_proposal_economy = "erc": [? if parlament_coalition_proposal_interior = "erc" or parlament_coalition_proposal_vp = "erc": and ?] giving up Economy ?]. We will have to wait until the [+ parlament_current_ciu +] and ERC negotiating teams reconvene to advance negotiations.

- @post_event: And so, time passes...


@accept
title: Accept proposal
choose-if: not parlament_coalition_changes and not parlament_coalition_concessions
unavailable-subtitle: We have proposed changes, which will require approval by [+ parlament_current_ciu +].
on-arrival: {!
    Q.ciu_erc_coalition_phase = 0;
    Q.cat_coalition_disp = "<span style='color: var(--" + Q.parlament_current_ciu + "); font-style: italic;'>Sovereignty</span> <span style='color: var(--erc); font-style: italic;'>government</span>";
    Q.erc_in_gob = true;
    Q.erc_supporting = true;
    Q.cat_coalition = [Q.parlament_current_ciu, "erc"];
    Q.cat_coalition_dissent = 0;

    Q.position_disp = "Generalitat";

    Q.cup_in_gob = false;
    Q.cup_supporting = false;
    
    Q.independence_trust += 10 * Q.erc_roadmap - (Q.year-2012);
!}

After some arduous negotiations, we have finally reached an agreement with [+ parlament_current_ciu +] to form a [+ cat_coalition_disp +]. Let's hope cooperation continues during this legislature, and that promises are kept!

- @parlament_coalition_resolve: A new government is formed


@new_elections
title: new elections
on-arrival: {!
    Q.ciu_erc_coalition_phase = 0;
    Q[Q.parlament_current_ciu + "_relations"] -= 5;
    Q.independence_trust -= 10;
    Q.snap_blame = Q.player_party;
    Q.snap_counterparty = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
    Q.snap_severity = 0.12;
!}
call: snap_election

After three rounds of negotiations, we've reached the end of the road. With no agreement in sight and no more time for back-and-forth, the only option left is to call for new elections and hope for a better result. Needless to say, neither [+ parlament_current_ciu +] nor the pro-independence groups are happy about this outcome.

- @post_event: We'll have to see if we fare any better this time...